---- About ----

This Nimrod module defines procedures and types for working with RSS.

---- Procedures ----

parseRSS(rss : string): TRSS
* Parses RSS from a string.

loadRSS(filename : string): TRSS
* Loads and parses RSS from a file.

getRSS(url : string): TRSS
* Gets and parses the RSS over HTTP.

---- Types ----

TRSSEnclosure
* Represents the <enclosure> sub-element of an <item>.
* Fields:
  url
  length
  enclosureType
(all fields are strings)

TRSSCloud
* Represents the <cloud> sub-element of a <channel>.
* Fields:
  domain
  port
  path
  registerProcedure
  protocol
(all fields are strings)

TRSSImage
* Represents the <image> sub-element of a <channel>.
* Fields:
  url
  title
  link
  width
  height
  description
(all fields are strings)

TRSSTextInput
* Represents the <textInput> sub-element of a <channel>.
* Fields:
  title
  description
  name
  link
(all fields are strings)

TRSSItem
* Represents an <item> sub-element of a <channel>.
* Fields:
  title
  link
  description
  author
  category : seq[string]
  comments
  enclosure : TRSSEnclosure
  guid
  pubDate
  sourceUrl
  sourceText
(all fields are strings unless otherwise stated)

TRSS
* Represents a <channel>.
* Fields:
  title
  link
  description
  language
  copyright
  managingEditor
  webMaster
  pubDate
  lastBuildDate
  category : seq[string]
  generator
  docs
  cloud : TRSSCloud
  ttl
  image : TRSSImage
  rating
  textInput : TRSSTextInput
  skipHours : seq[string]
  skipDays : seq[string]
  items : seq[TRSSItem]
(all fields are strings unless otherwise stated)

If the RSS document being parsed is missing an optional sub-element then the corrosponding field will not be set; there are no default values.

See the RSS 2.0 specification at http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/rss/rss.html for more information.

